          "summary": "Mixed but trending positive. Recurring technical friction throughout Q1 (PTO bugs, cache issues, schedule display, automated conflict handling). Spanish Fork is the most at-risk community \u2014 Blake reverted to a paper system for a month. The Apr 24 QBR was a genuine turning point: Ben Reeves engaged and enthusiastic, ROI data resonated, Workday integration scoped. Columbine Commons check-in on Apr 21 was collaborative. No confirmed real #at-risk signals (Highland Manor Fallon entries from March 30 appear to be test entries).",
